@startuml diagrama_despliegue
title Sistema de Gestión de Becas Universitarias — Diagrama de Despliegue

skinparam wrapWidth 220
skinparam node {
  BackgroundColor<<Docker Host>> #EAF4FF
  BorderColor<<Docker Host>> #4A78B5
}
skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor #FFF6D5
  BorderColor #C9A227
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #E8F5E9
  BorderColor #4C9A5A
}
skinparam artifact {
  BackgroundColor #ECECEC
  BorderColor #888888
}
skinparam storage {
  BackgroundColor #F3E8FF
  BorderColor #9B6FD1
}

actor "Estudiante / Operador / Director" as Usuario

artifact "Imagen Docker\n(docker/Dockerfile: python:3.12-slim\n+ requirements.txt + entrypoint.sh)" as ImgDev

' =====================================================================
node "Equipo de desarrollo — Docker Compose\n(docker-compose.yml)" <<Docker Host>> as DevHost {
  node "init\n<<container, one-shot>>\ncommand: migrate --noinput" as DevInit
  node "web\n<<container>>\ncommand: runserver 0.0.0.0:8000" as DevWeb
  node "worker\n<<container>>\ncommand: celery worker -l info" as DevWorker
  node "beat\n<<container>>\ncommand: celery beat\n--scheduler DatabaseScheduler" as DevBeat
  database "db\n<<container>>\nPostgreSQL 17-alpine" as DevDB
  node "redis\n<<container>>\nRedis 7.4-alpine" as DevRedis
  node "pgadmin\n<<container>>\npgAdmin4 (admin web BD)" as DevPgAdmin

  storage "postgres_data" as VolPG
  storage "media_data" as VolMedia
  storage "pgadmin_data" as VolPgAdmin
}

note bottom of DevHost
  web, worker y beat montan el código fuente (bind mount ".:/app")
  para hot-reload en desarrollo. Todos los servicios (init, web,
  worker, beat) se construyen desde la MISMA imagen; solo cambia
  el "command" de docker-compose.yml.
end note

' =====================================================================
cloud "Render — Producción\n(configurada manualmente, sin IaC)" as RenderCloud {
  node "becas-web\n<<Docker Web Service>>\ngunicorn config.wsgi:application" as ProdWeb
  node "becas-worker\n<<Docker Worker Service>>\ncelery worker -B\n(beat embebido, DatabaseScheduler)" as ProdWorker
  database "becas-db\n<<PostgreSQL 17 — managed>>" as ProdDB
  node "becas-redis\n<<Redis — managed>>" as ProdRedis
}

note bottom of RenderCloud
  Configurado manualmente desde el dashboard de Render — el
  blueprint render.yaml del repo NO está implementado/en uso.
  Sin Nginx: Render termina TLS y enruta directo a Gunicorn.
end note

' =====================================================================
node "Máquina externa (PC de escritorio)\n— docker-compose.worker.yml" as ExternalHost {
  node "worker\n<<container>>\ncelery worker -B\n(.env.worker)" as ExtWorker
}

note bottom of ExternalHost
  Conecta a la BD/Redis REALES de producción desde fuera de
  Render (.env.worker, no .env). Tráfico saliente hacia los
  endpoints externos de becas-db / becas-redis.
end note

cloud "Gmail SMTP\nsmtp.gmail.com:587 (TLS)" as SMTP

' =====================================================================
' Manifestación de artefactos: misma imagen, distintos nodos destino
ImgDev ..> DevInit : <<deploy>>
ImgDev ..> DevWeb : <<deploy>>
ImgDev ..> DevWorker : <<deploy>>
ImgDev ..> DevBeat : <<deploy>>
ImgDev ..> ProdWeb : <<deploy>>
ImgDev ..> ProdWorker : <<deploy>>
ImgDev ..> ExtWorker : <<deploy>>

' Comunicación en runtime + dependencia de arranque combinadas (dev)
DevInit --> DevDB : TCP/5432 (migrate)\ndepends_on: service_healthy
DevWeb --> DevDB : TCP/5432 (psycopg3)\ndepends_on: service_healthy
DevWorker --> DevDB : TCP/5432\ndepends_on: service_healthy
DevBeat --> DevDB : TCP/5432 (lee/escribe schedules)\ndepends_on: service_healthy
DevPgAdmin --> DevDB : TCP/5432 (admin)\ndepends_on: service_healthy

DevWeb --> DevRedis : TCP/6379\ndepends_on: service_healthy
DevWorker --> DevRedis : TCP/6379 (broker db1 / result db2)\ndepends_on: service_healthy
DevBeat --> DevRedis : TCP/6379\ndepends_on: service_healthy

' Dependencia pura de orquestación (sin comunicación posterior)
DevWeb ..> DevInit : depends_on\n(service_completed_successfully)
DevWorker ..> DevInit : depends_on\n(service_completed_successfully)
DevBeat ..> DevInit : depends_on\n(service_completed_successfully)

' Volúmenes (persistencia)
DevDB -- VolPG : monta
DevWeb -- VolMedia : monta
DevWorker -- VolMedia : monta
DevPgAdmin -- VolPgAdmin : monta

' Producción (Render)
ProdWeb --> ProdDB : TCP/5432
ProdWorker --> ProdDB : TCP/5432
ProdWeb --> ProdRedis : TCP (broker/result backend)
ProdWorker --> ProdRedis : TCP (broker/result backend)

' Worker externo -> servicios de producción
ExtWorker ..> ProdDB : TCP/5432 externo\n(.env.worker)
ExtWorker ..> ProdRedis : TCP externo\n(.env.worker)

' Notificaciones por correo (app notificaciones, vía Celery)
DevWorker ..> SMTP : SMTP/587 TLS
ProdWorker ..> SMTP : SMTP/587 TLS
ExtWorker ..> SMTP : SMTP/587 TLS

' Acceso de usuarios
Usuario --> DevWeb : HTTP\nlocalhost:8000 (solo dev)
Usuario --> ProdWeb : HTTPS\n*.onrender.com

legend right
  |= Notación |= Significado |
  | node | Host físico/virtual o contenedor Docker |
  | <<Docker Host>> | Máquina que ejecuta Docker Compose |
  | database | Servidor de base de datos (PostgreSQL) |
  | storage | Volumen de persistencia (Docker named volume) |
  | cloud | Servicio externo / PaaS fuera del control directo del repo |
  | artifact | Unidad desplegable (imagen Docker) |
  | --> (sólida) | Comunicación en tiempo de ejecución (protocolo indicado) |
  | ..> (punteada) | Dependencia de arranque/orquestación o <<deploy>> de artefacto |
  | depends_on: service_healthy | Espera healthcheck del contenedor destino |
  | depends_on: service_completed_successfully | Espera a que el contenedor one-shot termine OK |
endlegend

@enduml
